            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>she had no equal in appearance and constitution</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl>
                <ref target="#src_Нарт._сказ."/>
                <biblScope>25</biblScope>
            </bibl>
        </cit>
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>dæ zærdæmæ ma xæss mæ zærdæjy kond</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>не принимай близко к сердцу мой характер („устройство моего сердца“)</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>do not take my character to heart (“organization of my heart”)</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl>
                <ref target="#src_Коста"/>
                <biblScope>14</biblScope>
            </bibl>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Лексикализованное прош. причастие от <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kænyn"/>
        ‘делать’. Ср. %bсогдийскую%b прош. форму <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
            ><lang/><w>kwnd</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Gershevitch"
                /><biblScope>710</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>570</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">A lexicalized past participle from <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kænyn"/>
        ‘to do’. Cf. %bSogdian%b past form <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>kwnd</w></mentioned>
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Gershevitch"
                /><biblScope>710</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
